{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/pidfile"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Each running VM writes a PID file at","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~\/.spooktacular\/vms\/<name>.vm\/pid"},{"text":". The file contains the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"process ID of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"text":" process that owns the VM.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Other commands (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stop"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"list"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ip"},{"type":"text","text":") read the PID file to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"determine whether a VM is running and to signal the process."}]},{"anchor":"PID-File-Lifecycle","text":"PID File Lifecycle","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"type":"text","text":" writes the PID file before booting the VM."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"spook stop","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reads the PID file and sends SIGTERM."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"text":" installs a SIGTERM handler that gracefully","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"stops the VM, removes the PID file, and exits.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"co